snippet.title: Child Abduction Emergency (AMBER ALERT) VAN ZANDT COUNTY  Texas (Texas Statewide) NOAA Weather Radio
snippet.description: BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE AMARILLO TX 827 PM CDT WED MAY 13 2020 THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY. THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT NETWORK THE VAN ZANDT COUNTY SHERIFF`S OFFICE IS SEARCHING FOR WILLOW SIRMANS, WHITE, FEMALE, 14 YEARS OLD, HEIGHT 3 FEET, 75 POUNDS, STRAWBERRY BLONDE HAIR, BLUE EYES WITH BRACES ON HER TEETH. POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR AUSTEN WALKER, WHITE, MALE, 21 YEARS OLD, HEIGHT 5 FEET 9 INCHES, 140 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, GREEN EYES, TATTOO ON THE LEFT ARM, AND A TATTOO AND SCAR ON THE RIGHT ARM, IN CONNECTION WITH HER ABDUCTION. THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN GRAND SALINE, TEXAS. LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR IMMEDIATE DANGER. IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE VAN ZANDT COUNTY SHERIFFU2019S OFFICE. NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS VAN ZANDT COUNTY SHERIFFU2019S AT 903-567-4133.
